kafka-oauth-consumer.go
===================

The Kafka OAuth demo shows how a customer can authenticate their client via OAuth2 to Kafka and how they can read data from a Kafka topic API.

This is only a sample without support and liability to its correctness!

Prerequisite
------------

The code is based on Go 1.18 and the confluent-kafka-go v1.8.2.

Links:

* https://github.com/confluentinc/confluent-kafka-go

How to use
----------

In order to use the sample please change the following parameters.

  PushApiUrl = 'PUSH_API_URL'
  GroupId = 'YOUR_GROUP_ID'
  CertLocation = 'PATH_TO_CERT'
  TopicName = 'YOUR_TOPIC_NAME'
  AuthUrl = 'OAUTH_TOKEN_API_URL'
  ClientId = 'YOUR_CLIENT_ID'
  ClientSecret = 'YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET'


You also need to provide the the CA certificate location. The certificate file must be in PEM format.

  CertLocation = './ca.pem'

